        <bioghist id="ref8">
            <head>Historical Note</head>
            <p>The McLaughlin Air Service Company was a Manhattan-based aerial photography service.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref9">
            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The McLaughlin Air Service Photograph Collection spans the period from 1934-1969 and contains aerial photographs of New York City and surrounding areas. The bulk of the photographs were taken between 1940 and 1942, before the spurt of post-World War II development.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <arrangement id="ref10">
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>The collection is divided into two series:</p>
            <list type="ordered">
                <item>Series I. Prints</item>
                <item>Series II. Negatives</item>
            </list>
        </arrangement>
        <relatedmaterial id="ref62">
            <head>Related Material at the Department of Prints, Photographs, and Architectural Collections</head>
            <p>Other aerial views of New York City can be found in the Thomas Airviews Collection (PR 106).</p>
        </relatedmaterial>
        <separatedmaterial id="ref63">
            <head>Separated Material</head>
            <p>Negatives in Series II are cellulose nitrate and are kept in cold storage. Please see a reference librarian if you feel you need access to these negatives.</p>
        </separatedmaterial>
